{"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/cedaw-pocket-guide-pacific-parliamentarians", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "38d4659642c93b04aaacab992f420f73f3471ce39bdd17e4b4df3c52425c8a87"}, "3": {"node_id": "4450ceb1-590f-46f6-b561-67ea26542930", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/cedaw-pocket-guide-pacific-parliamentarians", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "c4c00e8f81c77b0195a5856f508cfb8db41eeedf468c54bb6975bf40958a2da3"}}, "hash": "b63c570da33151596c4be568d01d2aa5704d1da323bcb8f8b57f3b97c981e3e5", "text": "ask question of the bureaucracy regarding their allocations for CEDAW and tackling gender issues. It would be useful if a gender analysis of the budget was attached when the budget was tabled in Parliament or Congress. CEDAW: A Pocket Guide for Pacific Parliamentarians 16 When the legislature is considering the Budget, members can ask questions about expenditure on CEDAW implementation. These questions may be sectoraly focused, for example, regarding the health sector or rural employment. Or questions may focus on more administrative issues, for example, regarding support to the women\u2019s department. T he Public Accounts Committee, when reviewing past budget expenditure, can follow up on questions asked during the budget approval process. It is important to make sure the bureaucracy knows that legislators are committed to ensuring the implementation of CEDAW and will check to make sure that expenditures promote this objective. Ensure that a gender impact analysis (including an analysis of how the Bill promotes/ complies with CEDAW) is attached to the Budget Bill. During the Budget process, lobby to: Ring-fence\ufffda\ufffdproportion\ufffdof\ufffdministry/departmental\ufffdbudgets,\ufffd\uff